Product Description

Perry Performance Plus Surgical Gloves

McKesson Perry synthetic surgical gloves are made of 100% synthetic polyisoprene to help deliver the performance characteristics of natural rubber latex without the risk of natural rubber latex sensitization. SureFit technology enhances roll-down protection. Meets or exceeds ASTM surgical glove standards.

At a Glance:

  • Continuous polymer coating makes it easy to take them off or put them on
  • Sterilized with gamma radiation and without powder to reduce the chance of post-operative complications
  • Designed for single use and meets all ASTM surgical glove standards

Sterile Surgical Gloves

Keeps Hands Safe and Clean

Put the McKesson surgical gloves on before performing medical, scientific or other delicate work to create a barrier for the skin. They come sterilized with gamma radiation and have a cream color that helps identify glove breaks and minimize glare. The sterile gloves meet or exceed ASTM surgical glove standards. They are 9 mils thick at the fingertips, which protects bare skin while allowing maximum tactile sensitivity. Once you're done with the gloves, simply throw them away.

Strong and Reliable Material

Rely on the Performance Plus surgical gloves in several situations that require a strong yet flexible sterile latex material. They're powder-free, which helps stave off powder-related post-operative complications or reactions. Their smooth, anti-slip finish ensures the gloves don't catch or pull during procedures. The gloves come in unisex sizes to fit different hand types. These medical gloves have been Chemo tested.

Comfortable Wear

Enjoy a comfy but snug fit thanks to the gloves' SureFit technology. The technology enhances roll-down protection to make sure gloves stay in place as you move. Their beaded cuff keeps the gloves strong and secure, while stopping anything from dripping or getting inside. A continuous polymer coating makes the gloves wearable whether your hands are wet or dry. They come packaged in sterile right and left pairs to make it easy to get one glove for each hand.

About McKesson

For over 180 years, McKesson has supported providers with the medical supplies they need to care for patients and run a healthy business. McKesson offers more than 300,000 products from leading national brands as well as its own private product label, and a suite of services to help businesses and facilities provide quality care, improve business performance, and manage time and expenses. McKesson improves the business of healthcare to help everyone focus on what matters most: patient care.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
